{"format":1,"name":"Warm Lowpass","isInstrument":false,"explanation":"A gentle one-pole low-pass with output gain. Feed it one of the royalty-free samples, a test tone, your mic, or your own file to hear it work.","params":[{"name":"Gain","index":0,"min":0,"max":2,"default":1},{"name":"Cutoff","index":1,"min":0,"max":1,"default":1}],"wasmBase64":"","html":"<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><style>\n    body{margin:0;font:14px ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif;background:#0b0e14;color:#e7eef6;\n      display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:18px;padding:26px 28px}\n    h1{font-size:16px;margin:0 0 6px;letter-spacing:.04em;color:#ffb454}\n    label{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;font-size:13px;color:#aeb9cc}\n    label span{color:#e7eef6;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}\n    input[type=range]{width:100%;accent-color:#ffb454}\n  </style></head><body>\n    <h1>Warm Lowpass</h1>\n    <label>Gain<span id=\"v0\"></span>\n      <input type=\"range\" data-i=\"0\" min=\"0\" max=\"2\" step=\"0.001\" value=\"1\">\n    </label>\n    <label>Cutoff<span id=\"v1\"></span>\n      <input type=\"range\" data-i=\"1\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.001\" value=\"1\">\n    </label>\n    <script>\n      function ready(){\n        document.querySelectorAll('input[type=range]').forEach(function(r){\n          var i=+r.dataset.i, out=document.getElementById('v'+i);\n          function send(){ out.textContent=(+r.value).toFixed(2); window.vstai.setParam(i,+r.value); }\n          r.addEventListener('input',send); send();\n        });\n      }\n      if(window.vstai&&window.vstai.onReady) window.vstai.onReady(ready); else ready();\n    </script>\n  </body></html>","publishedAt":1750000001000,"assembly":"// =====================================================================\n//  AssemblyScript DSP module template  (compiles to WASM via `asc`)\n//\n//  This is the *shape* every Claude-generated module follows. It implements\n//  the ABI described in src/WasmAbi.h. The example DSP here is a simple\n//  stereo gain + one-pole low-pass so you can hear something immediately;\n//  Claude replaces the body of `process()` and the parameter wiring.\n//\n//  Rules the generated code must obey:\n//   - No imports. Self-contained. No host calls, no JS, no WASI.\n//   - Planar f32 buffers, layout: base + (channel * MAX_FRAMES + frame) * 4.\n//   - Never write past MAX_FRAMES / MAX_CHANNELS.\n//   - process() must be allocation-free and must not block.\n// =====================================================================\n\nconst MAX_FRAMES: i32 = 8192;\nconst MAX_CHANNELS: i32 = 2;\nconst MAX_PARAMS: i32 = 64;\n\n// --- Static buffers (their addresses never move after start) ----------\n// StaticArray<f32> stores its elements inline starting at the object\n// pointer, so changetype<usize>(buf) is the address of element 0.\nconst inBuf:  StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_FRAMES * MAX_CHANNELS);\nconst outBuf: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_FRAMES * MAX_CHANNELS);\nconst params: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_PARAMS);\n\n// --- DSP state --------------------------------------------------------\nlet sampleRate: f32 = 44100.0;\nlet channels: i32 = 2;\nlet lpState: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_CHANNELS);\n\n// Parameter indices (must match the indices the generated HTML sends).\nconst P_GAIN: i32 = 0;   // 0..2  (linear, 1 = unity)\nconst P_CUTOFF: i32 = 1; // 0..1  (1 = wide open)\n\n// --- ABI exports ------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport function init(sr: f32, maxFrames: i32, numChannels: i32): void {\n  sampleRate = sr;\n  channels = numChannels < MAX_CHANNELS ? numChannels : MAX_CHANNELS;\n  for (let c = 0; c < MAX_CHANNELS; c++) lpState[c] = 0.0;\n\n  // sensible defaults\n  params[P_GAIN] = 1.0;\n  params[P_CUTOFF] = 1.0;\n}\n\nexport function getInputPtr(): usize  { return changetype<usize>(inBuf); }\nexport function getOutputPtr(): usize { return changetype<usize>(outBuf); }\nexport function getParamsPtr(): usize { return changetype<usize>(params); }\nexport function getNumParams(): i32   { return 2; }\n\nexport function process(numFrames: i32): void {\n  const gain: f32 = params[P_GAIN];\n  // map cutoff 0..1 to a one-pole coefficient\n  const cutoff: f32 = params[P_CUTOFF];\n  const coeff: f32 = cutoff <= 0.0 ? 0.0 : (cutoff >= 1.0 ? 1.0 : cutoff);\n\n  for (let c = 0; c < channels; c++) {\n    const base: i32 = c * MAX_FRAMES;\n    let z: f32 = lpState[c];\n    for (let f = 0; f < numFrames; f++) {\n      const x: f32 = inBuf[base + f];\n      z = z + coeff * (x - z);     // one-pole low-pass\n      outBuf[base + f] = z * gain;\n    }\n    lpState[c] = z;\n  }\n}\n"}